{
    "description": "You need the div with class otkmodal to wrap the otkmodal-body when you implement your modal, however, to show you what a modal looks like we have commented it out for now.  As is, if you copy and paste this code into your website, the modal will be hidden",
    "html": "<!-- In order to display the modal, you need to add the otkmodal-isvisible class to fade it in, and then set the display to block on the modal-->\n<!--<div class=\"otkmodal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\" role=\"dialog\" aria-labelledby=\"myModalLabel\" aria-hidden=\"true\"> -->\n\n    <!-- this div below determines if the modal is actually a modal, it is the backdrop that masks the page -->\n    <!-- to show the backdrop you just need to add the class otkmodal-backdrop-isvisible -->\n    <div class=\"otkmodal-backdrop\"></div>\n    <div class=\"otkmodal-dialog otkmodal-md\">\n        <a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" class=\"otkmodal-close\" data-dismiss=\"otkmodal\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n            <i class=\"otkicon otkicon-closecircle\"></i>\n        </a>\n        <div class=\"otkmodal-content\">\n            <div class=\"otkmodal-header\">\n                <h4 class=\"otkmodal-title otktitle-2\" id=\"myModalLabel\">Log In To Origin</h4>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"otkmodal-body\">...</div>\n            <div class=\"otkmodal-footer\">\n                <a href=\"#\" class=\"otkbtn otkbtn-primary\">Click Me!</a>\n                <a href=\"#\" class=\"otkbtn otkbtn-light\">Do it</a>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n<!-- </div> -->"
}